parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the deployment of airbags without warning, causing injuries or fatalities, or the failure to deploy airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning indicator illuminates
airbags deploy without warning or impact
airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
and the vehicle's safety features are compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the recalled Takata airbags can lead to the deployment of airbags without warning, causing injuries or fatalities, or the failure to deploy airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning indicator illuminates
airbags deploy without warning or impact
airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
and the vehicle's safety features are compromised. Additionally
owners experience delays or unavailability of parts for the recall repair
leaving them at risk of injury or death.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and failure can cause the vehicle to stall or jerk, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when merging or changing lanes.
symptoms: The vehicle shutterers when accelerating from a stop
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle makes a noise when driving
acceleration is slow
the transmission fails to engage or pops back into neutral
the vehicle stalls or jerks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a crash
despite meeting the deployment criteria.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Hardness in Cold Temperatures
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal becoming extremely hard in cold temperatures can lead to reduced stopping power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal is rock solid or extremely hard when starting the car in cold temperatures (around 40Â°F or colder)
and then suddenly softens after pumping the brakes; in some cases
a brief grinding sound is heard while the pedal softens.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Sticking Gas Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine continuing to accelerate even when the gas pedal is not depressed, and the gas pedal sticking even after the foot is removed, can cause loss of control and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine continues to race even when the gas pedal is not depressed
the gas pedal seems to stick even after the foot is removed and placed on the brake pedal
and the vehicle accelerates unintentionally; this occurs intermittently without warning
regardless of speed.
